  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `geth version` 1.10.12\r\nOS & Version: Linux Ubuntu 18.04\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n      Once I start the eth node, and set the miner with \"--miner --miner.etherbase 'MyAccount' \",the miner of node should always be MyAccount.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n      The miner address was MyAccount initially, however, after about 2 minutes, the mineraddress was changed to \"0x1cffe205e97976bb9d1ec006f5222360a89353e0\". No matter how I reset the miner address to MyAccount, the miner address was always changed to 0x1cffe...\r\n      It happens not only in public chain, but also in private chain. I used the version from 1.10.6 to 1.10.12, every version has the same problem.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n      I used the start command \r\n`nohup   geth --syncmode \"full\" --port \"30303\" --cache=10240 --datadir MyDataDir --http --http.addr 0.0.0.0 --http.port 8545 --http.api debug,eth,net,web3,personal,admin,miner,txpool --ws --ws.addr 0.0.0.0 --ws.port 8546 --ws.api eth,net,web3,personal,admin,miner,txpool --mine --miner.etherbase 'MyAddressHere' --allow-insecure-unlock --maxpeers 10  --maxpendpeers 10 >> MyDataDir/geth.log 2>&1 &`\r\n      Also, geth command \r\n`miner.setEtherbase(eth.accounts[0])`\r\n      The commands can work only about 2 minutes, and then the miner address was changed to 0x1cffe...\r\n\r\n> > eth.coinbase\r\n> \"0x1cffe205e97976bb9d1ec006f5222360a89353e0\"\r\n> > miner.setEtherbase(eth.accounts[0])\r\n> true\r\n> > eth.coinbase\r\n> \"0xc3414...\"\r\n> > eth.coinbase\r\n> \"0x1cffe205e97976bb9d1ec006f5222360a89353e0\"\r\n",
